    slug: "essential-lessons-for-every-muslim",
    description: `Essential Lessons for Every Muslim is an English-language Islamic educational book that presents the foundational knowledge that every Muslim is obligated to learn and practice. The book is structured as a systematic curriculum of essential Islamic knowledge, covering the six pillars of faith (arkan al-iman), the five pillars of Islam (arkan al-Islam), the conditions and requirements of the testimony of faith (shahadah), the proper performance of ablution (wudu) and prayer (salah), and the basic rulings related to purification, fasting, charity, and pilgrimage. The content is drawn primarily from the works of the scholars of the Salafi methodology, with particular emphasis on the famous primer "Al-Usool Ath-Thalaatha" (The Three Fundamental Principles) by Shaykh Muhammad ibn Abdul Wahhab and related texts that have been used for centuries to teach new Muslims and young students the essentials of their religion.

The book organizes its material into clear, progressive lessons that build upon one another in a logical sequence. The first section addresses the three fundamental principles that every Muslim must know: knowledge of Allah, knowledge of the religion of Islam, and knowledge of the Prophet Muhammad (peace be upon him). Each principle is explained with supporting evidence from the Quran and hadith, and common misconceptions or deviations related to each principle are addressed with clarity and firmness. The subsequent sections cover the pillars of Islam in detail, with particular attention to the prayer, which the author treats with the thoroughness it deserves given its centrality in Muslim life. The description of the prayer includes the conditions (shuroot), the obligatory elements (arkan), the recommended acts (sunan), and the things that invalidate the prayer, along with clear diagrams or descriptions of the physical postures and movements.

This book is designed for a broad audience that includes new Muslims who need a structured introduction to their faith, Muslim parents who want to teach their children the fundamentals of Islam in an organized manner, Islamic school teachers who need a curriculum for introductory Islamic studies classes, and anyone who wants to review or solidify their understanding of the basic requirements of their religion. The English language used throughout is straightforward and precise, with Arabic terms transliterated and explained for readers who may not be familiar with Islamic terminology. The book has been widely used in English-speaking Muslim communities as a foundational text for dawah programs, new Muslim classes, and personal study, and its structured approach makes it an excellent reference that can be consulted repeatedly whenever questions arise about the essential knowledge that every Muslim is required to possess. The emphasis on evidence-based teaching ensures that readers are not merely memorizing rules but understanding the scriptural basis for what they believe and practice.`,
